## Free-first UX

- Empty states should link to `/admin` when cache or portfolio is empty.
- Show `meta.source` when present (`sqlite`, `sec_edgar`, `nasdaq`, `disabled`).
- Bootstrap/Reactstrap + DataGrid + ApexCharts; Redux only for screener state.

## High-density UI

- Preserve information-dense grids and compact layouts (research, screener, industry) â€” do not inflate spacing or strip columns for aesthetics.
- Heatmaps and conditional formatting via `heatMap.js` / `scoringColors.js`; metric keys from `config/metricRegistry.js`.
- No duplicate metric thresholds or composite scoring in page components.

## Performance (grids & screener)

- Memoize column defs and handlers; use stable dataset keys â€” **never `JSON.stringify(rows)` as a memo dependency**.
- Heavy stats (`columnMinMax`, percentiles): cache per dataset id (`heatmapCache.js` pattern).
- Profile before adding new memo/cache layers; precompute row heat styles in `useMemo`, not per-cell on sort.
- **Run React Profiler before and after** any change to DataGrid column definitions, heatmap rendering, or screener layout. Record render counts in the Phase 4 outcome summary.
- Run `e2e/large-grid.spec.js` when column definitions or heatmap logic changes.

## Prohibited patterns

| Pattern | Reason |
|---------|--------|
| `JSON.stringify(rows)` as a `useMemo`/`useCallback` dep | Defeats memoization; full re-render on every sort |
| Per-cell heatmap stat computation on each render | Use precomputed row-level stats in `useMemo` |
| Hardcoded scoring thresholds in page components | Breaks canonical `scoringColors.js` architecture |
| New metric threshold or composite formula outside `metricRegistry.js` | Creates divergent score semantics |
| `console.log` in render paths | Causes profiling noise; remove before commit |
| Hardcoded `/api/...` paths outside `apiConfig.js` | API paths must be centralized |

## Tests

- Unit: `npm test -- --watchAll=false`
- Full QA: `npm run qa:frontend`
